               <head>Qarabadin of Shifa'i</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kitāb-i Qarābādīn by Shifāʼī, Muẓaffar ibn Muḥammad, -1555 or 1556</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010106008 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083158" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16449-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>A well-known dictionary of compound medicaments (murakkabat). By Muẓaffar ibn Muḥammad Ḥusaynī Shifā’ī Kāshānī, known as Shifā’ī (d. 963/1556). For details, and a list of
                manuscripts and printed editions, see Storey PL II/2 E, pp. 245-6; Munzavī, FNKhF I, pp. 580-1.</p>
                        <p>Other BL manuscripts: Add. 23558, f. 306-361, Add. 26310 (Rieu BM II, pp. 852, 473); I.O. Islamic 1208, 1949 (defective), and 2367 (defective; see Ethé IOL I, cols. 1264-5).</p>
                        <p>Begins: Basmala 
                <q>al-Ḥamd li-Llāh al-‘Alīm al-Ḥakīm Va l-ṣalāt ‘alà man ūtiya l-ḥikma va l-Kitāb al-Karīm ... Ammā ba‘d Bar naẓar-i arbāb-i ḥazq pūshīda namānad ki faqīr-i ḥaqīr Muẓaffar ibn
                Muḥammad al-Ḥusaynī al-Shifā’ī dar muddat-i madīd tarkībī chand dar mu‘ālajat-i amrāż</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Ends: 
                <q>Sharāb-i anār-i ‘azb Az har (yak?) (sī?) misqāl ‘asal-i ṣāf ba-qadr-i iḥtiyāj ba-ṭarīq-i ma‘hūd ma‘jun sāzand sharbatī yakmisqāl ba‘d az chihil rūz Tammat</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Other contents: 1r, a bayt of mystical verse; 1r-1v, medicinal formulae; 99v-101v, an extract from a treatise on ophthalmology, briefly describing symptoms and treatments.</p>
                        <p>Undated: 13th/19th century.</p>
                        <p>Nasta‘līq. 17 lines. Red headings. Some folios tinted blue, others beige. Paper changes near end. 101 folios. 217 x 124 mm.; text lines 170 x 90 mm. Limp black goatskin covers.</p>
                        <p>Purchased from Mr H. T. Mohamad, 5 December 2007.</p>
